    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six power plant. This unit remains mechanically stout, benefiting from a comprehensive VANOS system refresh and a recent valve shim adjustment to ensure optimal valvetrain timing and compression. Crucially, the rear subframe mounting points have been reinforced with plates to address the chassis's inherent structural weak points. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M differential lock, providing exceptional mechanical grip. The suspension retains its factory-spec McPherson strut/multi-link geometry, offering precise turn-in and communicative feedback. While the exterior shows the honest patina of a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the drivetrain remains tight, and the throttle response from the individual throttle bodies is immediate. This is a driver-focused example ready for the apex.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Used car in good condition. Clean title. Maintenance records available. Reliable daily driver. Minor surface scratches only.",
      "price": 34500.0,
